Bungoma assembly speaker John Makali has urged the country to scrutinise the recently passed election laws to ensure Kenyans have confidence in the new IEBC team.Speaking on Thursday, he said free, fair and transparent election is crucial to avoid suspicion that has marred the political landscape. Makali said all political players must be involved in decision making. The Kanduyi MP hopeful urged Kenyans to elect leaders based on their track record. He hopes to run ion the ODM ticket.